results.notes:
Growing on petioles of dead Matteucia strutiopteris leaves on both dormant and leafy plants. Co-occuring on some plants with a white corticioid (DG2108083). Locally abundant. Yellowish-brown with lighter margins. Pendulous and growing in clusters. Basidiocarps 1.0 to 2.5 mm long and 0.5 to 1.1 mm wide. Context white. Odor not distinctive. All structures inamyloid. Clamps present. Hairs yellowish, smooth and thick-walled. Basidia 2-sterigmate to 4-sterigmate. Spores smooth, hyaline and thin-walled. Spore measurements: (8.7) 9.2 – 11.7 (12.9) × (3.2) 3.5 – 3.9 (4.3) µm, Q = (2.2) 2.4 – 3.3 (3.7); N = 30, Me = 10.5 × 3.7 µm; Qe = 2.9.

results.notes:
Growing on a mossy decorticated conifer log near Tsuga canadensis and Picea sp. Caps very pale brown (10YR 7/3 in Munsell) from the margins to the centers; centers dark brown (10YR 4/3); translucent-striate; convex to plane with depressed centers; smooth and dry; 3.3 to 6.5 mm wide and 1.5 to 2.6 mm tall. Gills light gray (10YR 7/2); decurrent with 1 to 2 tiers of lamellulae; some forked; even. Growing scattered in Sphagnum and dead grasses at the edge of a bog. Veils present in young caps. Clamps present in the lamellar trama. Cheilocystidia forming a sterile margin; hyaline, smooth, utriform and slightly thick-walled. Clamps present in the lamellar trama. Pleurocystidia scattered; mucronate, smooth and yellow with refractive content in 10% NH4OH. Cheilocystidia forming a sterile band; fusiform to utriform to lageniform; smooth, thin-walled and hyaline in 10% NH4OH. Basidia 2-sterigmate to 4-sterigmate. Spores brown, thick-walled, with prominent germ pores and finely roughened when viewed at 1000×. Spores purple-brown in mass. Spore measurements: (11.4) 12.5 – 15 (18.9) × (5.4) 6.1 – 7.4 (9) µm; Q = (1.7) 1.9 – 2.2 (2.3); N = 30; Me = 14 × 6.8 µm; Qe = 2.1.
